headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma scored 21 points and Thomas Bryant added 16, and the Washington Wizards won their 14th straight home meeting with Detroit, holding off the Pistons 116-113 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards beat Pistons for 14th straight time at home, 116-113

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 33 points, eight rebounds and seven assists to help the Boston Celtics rally in the second half and beat the Atlanta Hawks 107-98 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 33 to help Celtics push past Hawks 107-98

headlines.description: — Scottie Barnes had 18 points and 10 rebounds, Gary Trent Jr. scored 24 and the Toronto Raptors rallied to beat Brooklyn 109-108 on Tuesday night for their second win over the struggling Nets in two days.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raptors rally for 2nd straight win over struggling Nets

headlines.description: — Ivica Zubac had 22 points and 12 rebounds, and the Los Angeles Clippers pulled away in the third quarter and cruised to a 113-100 victory over the Houston Rockets on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zubac has 22 points to help Clippers rout Rockets 113-100

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns took this game over like the All-Star that he is. The Minnesota Timberwolves performed like the playoff team they're on track to be.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns has 39 points as Wolves surge past Warriors 129-114

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored seven of his 25 points in the fourth quarter, Jalen Brunson added 22 points and the Dallas Mavericks rallied for a 109-104 victory over the Los Angeles Lakers on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mavericks blow big lead, rally to hold off Lakers 109-104
